            <div id="id2" style="height: 66px; left: 28px; position: absolute; top: 1px; width: 642px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_2 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content Normal_External_642_66" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="Normal">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="Title">Here we shall learn how to calculate vibrations of an H<span style="line-height: 19px; " class="style_2">2</span>O molecule using the VASP code</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id3" style="height: 142px; left: 29px; position: absolute; top: 71px; width: 642px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_642_142" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style"><span class="style_3">The approach consists of three steps: <br /></span></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_1"><span class="style_3">  (i) run </span><span class="style_4">tetr</span><span class="style_3"> to prepare all the necessary input files and a script;</span><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_2"> <span class="style_5">(ii) run the script which will call </span><span class="style_6">VASP</span><span class="style_5">;</span><br /></p>
                  <p class="paragraph_style_3">(iii) run <span class="style_6">tetr </span>again to finish.<br /></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id4" style="height: 88px; left: 30px; position: absolute; top: 216px; width: 643px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_643_88" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style"><span class="style_7">1.</span><span class="style_3"> Start </span><span class="style_4">tetr</span><span class="style_3">. Read </span><span class="style_8">CONTCAR</span><span class="style_3"> file for the water molecule (below) using </span><span class="style_9">3</span><span class="style_3"> (</span><span class="style_4">VASP</span><span class="style_3"> input) of the entrance menu, followed by the species symbols </span><span class="style_9">O</span><span class="style_3"> and </span><span class="style_9">H</span><span class="style_3">.</span></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div style="height: 443px; width: 343px;  height: 443px; left: 322px; position: absolute; top: 534px; width: 343px; z-index: 1; " class="tinyText style_SkipStroke_4 stroke_0">
              <img src="1_files/Screen%20shot%202011-04-18%20at%2022.17.33.jpg" alt="" style="border: none; height: 444px; width: 343px; " />
            </div>
            


            <div id="id5" style="height: 42px; left: 28px; position: absolute; top: 1069px; width: 650px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_650_42" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style"><span class="style_7">5.</span><span class="style_3"> Use </span><span class="style_9">Sy</span><span class="style_3"> to check the symmetry of the molecule (below):</span> </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div style="height: 305px; width: 439px;  height: 305px; left: 140px; position: absolute; top: 1116px; width: 439px; z-index: 1; " class="tinyText style_SkipStroke_4 stroke_1">
              <img src="1_files/Screen%20shot%202011-04-18%20at%2022.19.25.jpg" alt="" style="border: none; height: 306px; width: 439px; " />
            </div>
            


            <div id="id6" style="height: 61px; left: 27px; position: absolute; top: 1437px; width: 650px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_650_61" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style"><span class="style_3">It is found to be C</span><span style="line-height: 17px; " class="style_10">2v</span><span class="style_3"> which 4 irreducible one-dimensional representations (irreps) called A1, A2, B1 and B2. </span></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id7" style="height: 88px; left: 28px; position: absolute; top: 1517px; width: 650px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_650_88" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style"><span class="style_7">6.</span><span class="style_3"> Atoms of the molecule are split into orbits (stars) of atoms which transform into each other via symmetry operations. Use option </span><span class="style_9">Co</span><span class="style_3"> to see this division for the water (below):</span></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div style="height: 101px; width: 629px;  height: 101px; left: 32px; position: absolute; top: 1619px; width: 629px; z-index: 1; " class="tinyText style_SkipStroke_4 stroke_2">
              <img src="1_files/Screen%20shot%202011-04-18%20at%2022.23.50.jpg" alt="" style="border: none; height: 101px; width: 630px; " />
            </div>
            


            <div id="id8" style="height: 88px; left: 25px; position: absolute; top: 869px; width: 285px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_285_88" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span class="style_11">3.</span> Use <span class="style_12">Q</span> to return to the main menu.<br /></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id9" style="height: 276px; left: 31px; position: absolute; top: 562px; width: 274px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_274_276" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span class="style_11">2.</span> Once in the main menu, use <span class="style_12">M</span> to go to the M menu. Use options there to preview the molecule with <a title="http://www.nongnu.org/xmakemol/" href="http://www.nongnu.org/xmakemol/" style="line-height: 26px; " class="style_13">xmakemol</a><span style="line-height: 26px; " class="style_14">. Make sure that you see that </span><span class="style_3">the molecule has the Z-axis as its 2nd order symmetry axis, and all atoms are positioned within the XZ plane. </span></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div id="id10" style="height: 277px; left: 30px; position: absolute; top: 1732px; width: 637px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_637_277" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style"><span class="style_3">As expected, there are 2 orbits:  one consisting of a single atom (oxygen), and one consisting of two H atoms. All three atoms are allowed to move in this case (not “fixed”). Note that in this case translations and rotation of the molecule as a whole (3+3 = 6 degrees of freedom in total) should be removed from all 9 degrees of freedom the molecule has. Therefore, there should be exactly 3 degrees of freedom left for the vibrations, i.e. three frequencies will be calculated  corresponding to 3 normal vibrations.</span><br /></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


            <div style="height: 149px; width: 390px;  height: 149px; left: 25px; position: absolute; top: 340px; width: 390px; z-index: 1; " class="tinyText style_SkipStroke_4 stroke_3">
              <img src="1_files/Screen%20shot%202011-04-18%20at%2023.01.28.jpg" alt="" style="border: none; height: 150px; width: 390px; " />
            </div>
            


            <div id="id11" style="height: 61px; left: 29px; position: absolute; top: 1000px; width: 647px; z-index: 1; " class="style_SkipStroke_3 shape-with-text">
              <div class="text-content graphic_textbox_layout_style_default_External_647_61" style="padding: 0px; ">
                <div class="graphic_textbox_layout_style_default">
                  <p style="padding-bottom: 0pt; padding-top: 0pt; " class="paragraph_style_3"><span class="style_11">4.</span> Once back in the main menu, use <span class="style_12">Vm</span> which will take you to the screen on your right. </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            


